        <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
            <head>Biography of Oscar A. Thompson</head><p>Oscar A. Thompson was involved in oil drilling activity in Wyoming and Montana.</p>
            
        </bioghist> 
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
            <head>Scope and Content</head><p>The collection contains two petroleum maps, three miscellaneous pamphlets, and photographs of oil field activity in the Little Buck Creek, Lance Creek, and Kevin-Sunburst oil fields. There is also an exploration memorandum (1956) from the Billings Division of the Montana Oil and Gas Conservation Commission regarding drilling for oil in a geologic formation in Montana, with accompanying handwritten drilling notes.</p>
            
        </scopecontent> 
